{% block containment %}
{# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   SECTION 5 · CONTAINMENT STEPS
   ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
## 🚨 Containment Steps

> **⚡ Execute steps in order. Mark each checkbox as complete. Escalate immediately if any step fails.**

{% if attack_pattern | default("") in ["brute_force", "failed_login"] %}
### Phase 1 – Immediate Isolation (T+0 to T+5 min)

- [ ] **Block attacker IP** – Apply ACL rule to block `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` on all perimeter devices for `{{ block_duration | default("3600") }}s`.
- [ ] **Enable tarpit** – Slow-respond to `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` with `{{ tarpit_delay_ms | default(5000) }}ms` delay to waste attacker resources.
- [ ] **Invalidate compromised sessions** – Force-expire all active sessions for accounts targeted in this brute-force attempt.
- [ ] **Reset at-risk credentials** – Identify accounts with login attempts from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` and trigger mandatory password reset.

### Phase 2 – Investigation (T+5 to T+30 min)

- [ ] **Query threat intelligence** – Submit `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` to VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, and internal threat-intel feed.
- [ ] **Pull authentication logs** – Retrieve the last `{{ log_lookback_hours | default(24) }}` hours of auth logs from all systems targeted.
- [ ] **Identify affected accounts** – List all user accounts that received login attempts from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}`.
- [ ] **Check for lateral movement** – Search SIEM for any successful logins from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` within the timeframe.

### Phase 3 – Remediation & Hardening (T+30 min onward)

- [ ] **Create incident ticket** – Open ticket in `{{ ticket_system | default("Jira") }}` with summary: *"Brute Force Attack: {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}"*.
- [ ] **Enable MFA** – Enforce MFA on all accounts accessed within the `{{ timeframe | default("attack timeframe") }}`.
- [ ] **Update firewall rules** – Add `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` and its subnet to the permanent block list.
- [ ] **Review account lockout policy** – Confirm lockout threshold ≤ `{{ failed_logins_threshold | default(20) }}` failed attempts.

{% elif attack_pattern | default("") in ["port_scan", "scan"] %}
### Phase 1 – Immediate Capture (T+0 to T+5 min)

- [ ] **Start packet capture** – Begin PCAP on all interfaces facing `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` for `{{ capture_duration | default("300s") }}`.
- [ ] **Deploy honeypots** – Spin up `{{ honeypot_count | default(3) }}` additional `{{ honeypot_type | default("deception_mesh") }}` honeypot nodes in the scanned subnet.
- [ ] **Activate aggressive deception** – Switch honeypot response mode to `{{ deception_mode | default("aggressive_deception") }}` to gather more attacker fingerprints.
- [ ] **Rate-limit scanner** – Apply rate-limit rule: max `{{ rate_limit_pps | default(10) }}` packets/sec from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}`.

### Phase 2 – Investigation (T+5 to T+30 min)

- [ ] **Analyse scan pattern** – Identify scan type (SYN, UDP, XMAS, FIN) from PCAP data and determine targeted ports.
- [ ] **Map exposed services** – Cross-reference scanned ports against production service inventory to identify exposure.
- [ ] **Alert SOC** – Send `{{ alert_level | default("HIGH") }}` alert to SOC: *"Port scan from {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} – {{ port_count_threshold | default(50) }}+ ports targeted."*
- [ ] **Query threat intel** – Look up `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` in threat feeds for known scanner / botnet membership.

### Phase 3 – Remediation (T+30 min onward)

- [ ] **Patch exposed services** – Review findings and patch or disable any unintended services discovered during scan analysis.
- [ ] **Update IDS/IPS signatures** – Add scanner fingerprint to IDS/IPS for early detection of follow-up exploitation.
- [ ] **Firewall tighten** – Block `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` subnet on perimeter for `{{ block_duration | default("86400") }}s`.
- [ ] **Document reconnaissance map** – Archive PCAP and port inventory in incident records.

{% elif attack_pattern | default("") in ["credential_reuse", "honeytoken"] %}
### Phase 1 – Critical Isolation (T+0 to T+2 min) ⚠️ CRITICAL

- [ ] **🔴 CISO Alert** – Immediately notify CISO and security lead: *"Honeytoken `{{ token_id | default("<token_id>") }}` used from non-honeypot IP `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}`."*
- [ ] **Isolate compromised host** – Network-isolate `{{ target_ip | default("<target_ip>") }}` immediately. Rollback: `reconnect_host`.
- [ ] **Revoke honeytoken** – Invalidate credential `{{ token_id | default("<token_id>") }}` across all systems immediately.
- [ ] **Block source IP** – Block `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` on all network segments.

### Phase 2 – Forensic Investigation (T+2 to T+60 min)

- [ ] **Full system scan** – Run `{{ scan_depth | default("full") }}` depth scan on `{{ target_ip | default("<target_ip>") }}`.
- [ ] **Capture forensic artefacts** – Collect `{{ forensic_artifacts | default(["memory", "process_list", "network_conns"]) | join(", ") }}` from `{{ target_ip | default("<target_ip>") }}`.
- [ ] **Timeline reconstruction** – Build event timeline from authentication, process, and network logs.
- [ ] **Scope credential exposure** – Audit all systems where the leaked credential was valid.

### Phase 3 – Recovery (T+60 min onward)

- [ ] **Rotate all shared secrets** – Rotate all credentials, API keys, and service accounts on `{{ target_ip | default("<target_ip>") }}`.
- [ ] **Re-image if necessary** – If persistence indicators found, re-image the compromised host.
- [ ] **Deploy new honeytokens** – Replace compromised honeytoken with fresh bait credentials.
- [ ] **Post-incident review** – Schedule 48-hour post-incident review with security team.

{% elif attack_pattern | default("") in ["distributed_attack", "distributed"] %}
### Phase 1 – Campaign Identification (T+0 to T+10 min)

- [ ] **Correlate events** – Run SIEM correlation rule for pattern `{{ attack_pattern | default("<attack_pattern>") }}` to identify all participating IPs.
- [ ] **Identify campaign scope** – Determine if `{{ distinct_ips_threshold | default(5) }}+ IPs` are from same ASN / botnet / campaign.
- [ ] **Escalate defensive posture** – Raise global security level to `{{ security_level | default("ENHANCED") }}`.
- [ ] **Enable DDoS mitigation** – Activate upstream scrubbing if traffic volume is impacting production systems.

### Phase 2 – Blocking & IOC Sharing (T+10 to T+30 min)

- [ ] **Block all campaign IPs** – Apply bulk block for `{{ block_duration | default("86400") }}s` to all identified attacker IPs.
- [ ] **Export IOCs** – Generate `{{ ioc_format | default("STIX") }}` IOC bundle and share with `{{ ioc_destination | default("threat_intel_sharing") }}`.
- [ ] **Notify ISP / upstream** – Report botnet campaign to ISP for upstream null-routing.
- [ ] **Activate geo-blocking** – If campaign originates from specific region, apply temporary geo-block.

### Phase 3 – Campaign Reporting (T+30 min onward)

- [ ] **Generate campaign report** – Produce full report at `reports/distributed_attack_{{ timestamp | default("<timestamp>") }}.md`.
- [ ] **Share IOCs with ISAC** – Submit IOC bundle to relevant Information Sharing and Analysis Centre.
- [ ] **Update threat model** – Record new TTPs in threat model and adjust detection thresholds.
- [ ] **Schedule tabletop exercise** – Plan distributed-attack tabletop with IR team within 2 weeks.

{% else %}
### Phase 1 – Immediate Response (T+0 to T+10 min)

{% if containment_steps is defined and containment_steps %}
{% for step in containment_steps %}
- [ ] **{{ step.name | default("Step") }}** – {{ step.description | default("Execute containment action.") }}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
- [ ] **Identify and isolate** – Determine affected systems and isolate from the network.
- [ ] **Preserve evidence** – Capture logs, memory dumps, and network traffic before any remediation.
- [ ] **Alert security team** – Notify SOC of the `{{ severity | default("HIGH") }}` severity incident.
- [ ] **Begin investigation** – Assign incident commander and open investigation ticket.
- [ ] **Collect IOCs** – Gather all IPs, domains, file hashes, and behavioural indicators.
- [ ] **Patch or remove vulnerability** – Address the root cause of the incident.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

